@NODE an.en "Overview"
@TOC Main.en
This programm compresses the reloctable of any executeables, libs, devices
and all codesegments. Started with this version (1.5) of the programm the
hunk will be splitted when it was greater then 64kByte, this makes possible
to convert greater programms too. The idea is very simple, the kickstart 2.0
and higher have a enhanced LoadSeg() funktion (Hunk_reloc32short), this makes
it possible to compress the reloc hunk`s (without modify the programmcode
self !!!).

Advantage: The reloctables are very short, speed up the funktion LoadSeg().
The programmcodes are NOT modified !!!

Disadvantage: This idea only runs under Kick 2.0+. It works only with short
porgramms (Hunksize lower then 64kByte). When the reloc-hunks are greater then
64k the programm will "split" into a second reloc-hunk. Cruncher Imploader
don`t understand the hunks ($3F7 & $3FC), but LHA and LZX are working !!!
(Problems only with selfextracting cruncher !!!)


