@NODE syn.en "Syntax"
@TOC Main.en

Syntax: 
        HunkShort Inputfile/A,Outputfile/A,OS3/S,ND=NoDebug/S,R32=Reclo32/S,
                  HN=HunkName/S

        Inputfile/A

               The inputfile...

        Outputfile/A

               The outputfile...

        OS3/S *
                
               This switch generates the orginal reloc32short hunk
               ($3FC). Programms with this hunk will be crash at
               kick2.0 and only work with 3.0+ (bug in the Kickstart)

        ND=NoDebug/S

               Don`t removes the debuginformations from the file.
               DPaintV saves in this hunk the userdata, and when
               this hunk removed, Dpaint will not run !!!

        R32=Reloc32/S

               Converts reloc32short into reloc32 and "decompressed"
               the file.

        HN=HunkName/S *

               This argument removes hunknames from the file...
               Mostly the hunk used as a self-protection against
               viruses.

        * Don`t use this switches when you don`t know about them !!!

@ENDNODE
